# Styling Conventions — Tailwind CSS v4

## Color Palette (Design Tokens)

This project uses a dark navy, blue, and sky blue palette. Always use CSS custom properties defined in `globals.css` — never hardcode hex values in components.

```css
/* src/styles/globals.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

:root {
  /* ─── Brand Colors (Exact — never change these values) ─── */
  --color-navy: #001439; /* Deep navy — primary background, hero, section bg */
  --color-blue: #2a8cd5; /* Brand blue — buttons, links, active states, icons */
  --color-sky: #9fccff; /* Light sky blue — headings, highlights, hover, accents */

  /* ─── Derived Tokens (built from brand colors) ─── */
  --color-bg-primary: #001439; /* = --color-navy */
  --color-bg-secondary: #001d52; /* navy lightened slightly for section alternation */
  --color-bg-card: #002060; /* card / surface — navy family */
  --color-bg-overlay: rgba(
    0,
    20,
    57,
    0.85
  ); /* navy with opacity — for overlays */

  --color-accent: #2a8cd5; /* = --color-blue — primary interactive color */
  --color-accent-hover: #1e6fab; /* blue darkened for hover states */

  --color-highlight: #9fccff; /* = --color-sky — headings, labels, badges */
  --color-highlight-muted: rgba(
    159,
    204,
    255,
    0.15
  ); /* sky with opacity — bg tints */

  --color-text-primary: #ffffff; /* White — body text on dark backgrounds */
  --color-text-secondary: #9fccff; /* Sky blue — subheadings, captions, labels */
  --color-text-muted: rgba(
    159,
    204,
    255,
    0.6
  ); /* Dimmed sky — placeholders, hints */

  --color-border: rgba(
    42,
    140,
    213,
    0.25
  ); /* Blue with low opacity — subtle borders */
  --color-border-strong: #2a8cd5; /* Full blue — focused borders, dividers */
}
```

