## Typography — Fonts

### Font Assignments

| Font         | Usage                               | Applied to                                                                            |
| ------------ | ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Segoe UI** | Headers, titles, navigation, labels | `h1` `h2` `h3` `h4` `h5` `h6`, nav items, section titles, card titles, button text    |
| **Inter**    | Body text, descriptions, paragraphs | `p`, descriptions, captions, form inputs, list items, any generated or long-form text |

### Font Setup in `globals.css`

Segoe UI is a system font (available on Windows/macOS). Inter is loaded via `next/font`.

```css
/* src/styles/globals.css */

/* Font family stacks */
:root {
  --font-header:
    "Segoe UI", "Segoe UI Web (West European)", system-ui, -apple-system,
    sans-serif;
  --font-body: "Inter", system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
}

/* Apply globally */
body {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  background-color: var(--color-bg-primary);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

h1,
h2,
h3,
h4,
h5,
h6 {
  font-family: var(--font-header);
  color: var(--color-sky);
}
```

### Inter via `next/font` in Root Layout

```jsx
// src/app/layout.jsx
import { Inter } from "next/font/google";

const inter = Inter({
  subsets: ["latin"],
  variable: "--font-inter",
  display: "swap",
});

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" className={inter.variable}>
      <body>{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

### Tailwind Font Utility Classes

```jsx
// ✅ Headers — Segoe UI
<h1 className="font-['Segoe_UI'] text-4xl font-bold text-[#9FCCFF]">
<h2 className="font-['Segoe_UI'] text-3xl font-semibold text-[#9FCCFF]">

// ✅ Body / descriptions — Inter
<p className="font-['Inter'] text-base text-white">
<p className="font-['Inter'] text-sm text-[#9FCCFF]">

// ✅ Using CSS variables (preferred)
<h2 className="text-3xl font-semibold" style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-header)', color: 'var(--color-highlight)' }}>
<p className="text-base" style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-body)' }}>
```

