## Spacing & Layout Conventions

| Purpose                | Classes                                          |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| Page section padding   | `py-16 md:py-24`                                 |
| Content container      | `container mx-auto px-4 md:px-8`                 |
| Card padding           | `p-6`                                            |
| Section header spacing | `mb-12`                                          |
| Grid gaps              | `gap-6` or `gap-8`                               |
| Responsive grid        | `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` |

---

## Responsive Breakpoints (Tailwind defaults)

| Prefix   | Min-width | Use case       |
| -------- | --------- | -------------- |
| _(none)_ | 0px       | Mobile first   |
| `sm:`    | 640px     | Large phones   |
| `md:`    | 768px     | Tablets        |
| `lg:`    | 1024px    | Small desktops |
| `xl:`    | 1280px    | Desktops       |
| `2xl:`   | 1536px    | Large screens  |

Always write **mobile-first**: start with the mobile class, then add responsive prefixes.

```jsx
// ✅ Mobile first
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

// ❌ Desktop first (wrong approach)
<div className="grid grid-cols-3 sm:grid-cols-1">
```

---

## What NOT to Do

- ❌ Never use colors outside the 3-brand palette (`#001439`, `#2A8CD5`, `#9FCCFF`) and their derived tokens
- ❌ Never use Tailwind's built-in color classes like `bg-blue-700`, `text-sky-400`, `bg-gray-900` — always use brand hex values
- ❌ Never use inline `style={{ color: '...' }}` for arbitrary colors — use the token variables
- ❌ Never create a separate CSS module file — Tailwind utility classes only
- ❌ Never use `@apply` except in `globals.css` for base resets
- ❌ Never use Inter for headings — Segoe UI only for headers
- ❌ Never use Segoe UI for body/description text — Inter only for paragraphs and descriptions
